<para id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.qualityAttributes.scalability.introParagraph"
  xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" 
  xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.solms.co.za/schemas/doc/solmsDoc/solmsDoc.xsd" 
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  Scalability refers to the ability to scale to increasing and potentially decreasing load. It is
  typically measured in terms of number of service requests which could be processed within a period
  or the number of concurrent users/clients which can be served.
</para>  